# MCP, PRD & Consciousness Stream (Manual Rule)

Invoke via `@850-mcp-and-prd` when planning architecture, MCP setup, or capturing team learnings.

## Product Requirements

Before structural or architectural changes:

1. Read `@docs/PRD.md`
2. Cross-check `@ARCHITECTURE.md` and relevant `@docs/ADR/*`
3. Confirm change aligns with offline-first non-goals

## Consciousness Stream

Append durable decisions and agent learnings to `@.notes/meeting_notes.md`:

```markdown
## Agent-Learnings
2026-05-22 — Lesson — Created 120-rag-workers.mdc after worker boundary fix
```

Do not store secrets in meeting notes.

## MCP Servers (StudyForge — Solo-Dev)

| Server | Purpose | Config | Hardware |
|--------|---------|--------|----------|
| **graphify-studyforge** | AST knowledge graph MCP | `.mcp.example.json` | Low-end OK |
| **code-review-graph** | Embeddings, impact radius | `.mcp.example.full.json` | 16GB+ RAM only |
| **github** (optional) | Issues, PRs | `~/.cursor/mcp.json` | — |
| **browser** (optional) | PWA debug | User global | — |

### Setup (low-end default)

```bash
pip install graphifyy
npm run graphify:refresh
cp .mcp.example.json .cursor/mcp.json
```

Enable **graphify-studyforge** in Cursor Settings → MCP. Do **not** run `graphify hook install` or `graphify watch` on this project.

Full profile (optional): `cp .mcp.example.full.json .cursor/mcp.json`

Policy: `@docs/GRAPHIFY.md`, rule `@105-graphify-solo-dev.mdc`

### Graph-First Workflow (token-efficient)

1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md`
2. MCP graphify or `graphify query --budget 1500`
3. Targeted file reads — avoid repo-wide grep on low-end sessions

### Remote Snapshot

Only `graphify-out/graph.json` + `GRAPH_REPORT.md` are pushed to GitHub (latest snapshot, no graph history).

## Legacy Prohibition

Do not create or commit `.cursorrules`. Use modular `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` only.
